tmjos-os-identity (2.0.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * Rebase da identidade do sistema para TMJOs 2.0 alpha em Debian 13
    trixie.
  * /etc/os-release agora usa ID_LIKE=debian, DEBIAN_CODENAME=trixie
    e TMJOS_CODENAME=insano.
  * /etc/lsb-release, /etc/issue e /etc/issue.net atualizados para
    v2.0 alpha, removendo os valores Ubuntu noble da linha v1.x.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Tue, 12 May 2026 23:00:00 -0300

tmjos-os-identity (1.3.0-2) noble; urgency=high

  * Fix install conflict with base-files. Previous version (1.3.0-1)
    declared `Conflicts: base-files (<< 999~)` to take ownership of
    /etc/os-release, lsb-release, issue, issue.net. base-files is
    Essential — apt refuses to remove it, so the conflict broke the
    install entirely:
        E: Unable to correct problems, you have held broken packages.
  * Refactored to use dpkg-divert (same approach as
    tmjos-shell-tweaks for Yaru's gnome-shell.css). Files now ship
    in /usr/share/tmjos-os-identity/ and the postinst diverts each
    target path, renaming the upstream file with .tmjos-orig suffix.
  * postrm restores the originals byte-for-byte on remove/purge.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 20:15:00 -0300

tmjos-os-identity (1.3.0-1) noble; urgency=low

  * Initial .deb release.
  * Replaces what customize.sh phase 6c/6d wrote inline.
  * /etc/os-release pinned to "TMJOs 1.3 (insano)".
  * /etc/lsb-release intentionally left as Ubuntu/noble for compat.
  * /etc/issue + /etc/issue.net branded.
  * (Broken: Conflicts: base-files isn't installable; replaced
    in 1.3.0-2.)

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 18:45:00 -0300
